.TH SENTINELBOX 1 "May 2026" "SentinelBox 1.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sentinelbox \- semantic-aware, rootless sandbox for secure AI code execution

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sentinelbox
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \-\- \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sentinelbox
is an advanced isolation engine designed for executing untrusted, AI-generated code. It implements a "Semantic Feedback Loop" using the Model Context Protocol (MCP) to translate raw kernel errors into actionable feedback for LLMs.

The sandbox utilizes a combination of Linux Kernel features:
.TP
\(bu 2
\fBNamespaces\fR: Isolation for PID, Mount, Network, IPC, UTS, and User views.
.TP
\(bu 2
\fBSeccomp User Notification\fR: High-performance syscall interception redirected to a User Space monitor.
.TP
\(bu 2
\fBOverlayFS & tmpfs\fR: Instantaneous environment resets using a RAM-backed writable layer.
.TP
\(bu 2
\fBCgroup v2\fR: Precise resource metering and hard limits for CPU and Memory.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-profile=\fINAME\fR
Apply security constraints from \fIprofiles/NAME.json\fR. Default: \fBstrict\fR.
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-profile\-dir=\fIDIR\fR
Directory containing JSON profile definitions. Default: \fI./profiles\fR.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-rootfs=\fIPATH\fR
\fBRequired.\fR The base read-only filesystem (lowerdir) for the OverlayFS mount.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-monitor=\fIPATH\fR
Path to the \fBsentinelbox-monitor\fR binary.
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-cgroup\-parent=\fIPATH\fR
Specify the parent cgroup node. Recommended for rootless environments.
.TP
.BR \-N ", " \-\-no\-monitor
Degrade to pure kernel-level enforcement without semantic feedback.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging on \fIstderr\fR.

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
\fBSENTINELBOX_LOG\fR
Log level for the monitor (\fIerror\fR, \fIwarn\fR, \fIinfo\fR, \fIdebug\fR, \fItrace\fR).
.TP
\fBSENTINELBOX_DB\fR
Path to the SQLite audit database. Default: \fI./sentinelbox.db\fR.
.TP
\fBSENTINELBOX_MAPPINGS\fR
Path to the JSON mapping for semantic feedback.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Execute a basic command in a restricted environment:
.RS
.B sentinelbox --rootfs=./rootfs/busybox -- /bin/sh -c "echo Hello"
.RE
.PP
Run a task that triggers a security violation:
.RS
.B sentinelbox --profile=strict --rootfs=./rootfs/busybox -- /bin/sh -c "nc example.com 80"
.RE

.SH BUGS
On some WSL2 or Docker environments, Cgroup creation may fail due to delegation restrictions. SentinelBox will automatically fall back to global host metrics to ensure the dashboard remains functional.

